Description: CVE-2026-28689 - Fix TOCTOU symlink race in path policy bypass
 ImageMagick path policy TOCTOU symlink race bypass. Prior to version
 6.9.13-41, domain='path' authorization is checked before the final file
 open/use. A symlink swap between check-time and use-time bypasses
 policy-denied read/write operations. This patch adds O_NOFOLLOW to file
 opens when symlink policy denies following, and re-checks path policy
 after files are opened to mitigate the race window.
 .
 Adapted for Debian bookworm (6.9.11-60): close_utf8() replaced with
 close() as it does not exist in this version; config/policy-secure.xml
 hunk redirected to config/policy.xml; context lines adjusted to match
 target version.
Origin: upstream, https://github.com/ImageMagick/ImageMagick6/commit/540a4126f39a0b09ae68ccd43ae6de21092b4b3a
Author: Cristy <urban-warrior@imagemagick.org>
Last-Update: 2026-03-11

