+
+# Why CVE-2026-25967 Does NOT Affect Debian Bookworm (ImageMagick 6.9.11.60)
+
+## Overview: What Is CVE-2026-25967?
+
+CVE-2026-25967 is a **stack-based buffer overflow** (CWE-787 / CWE-121) in the ImageMagick **FTXT image reader**. A crafted FTXT file can cause out-of-bounds writes on the stack via the `ReadInt()` function in `coders/ftxt.c`, potentially leading to a crash. It carries a CVSS v3.1 score of **7.4 (High)** with network attack vector. The fix (commit `9afe96cc325da1e4349fbd7418675af2f8708c10`) changes a `continue` to `break` in the buffer bounds check so the read loop terminates instead of overflowing the stack buffer.
+
+Reference: [GHSA-72hf-fj62-w6j4](https://github.com/ImageMagick/ImageMagick/security/advisories/GHSA-72hf-fj62-w6j4)
+
+---
+
+## Why CVE-2026-25967 Does NOT Affect Debian Bookworm
+
+Security scanners may flag **CVE-2026-25967** for ImageMagick, but for Debian Bookworm (`imagemagick` source `6.9.11.60+dfsg`):
+
+- The patch for this CVE targets `coders/ftxt.c` (`ReadInt()` function)
+- `coders/ftxt.c` is **not present** in this source package
+- The `ReadInt()`, `ReadChar()`, and all FTXT-related symbols do not exist in this codebase
+- No reference to "FTXT" or "ftxt" exists in `configure.ac`, `coders/Makefile.am`, or anywhere in the source tree
+- The FTXT coder was introduced in **ImageMagick 7.x only** and was never backported to the 6.x branch
+- The Debian security tracker confirms the only fixed version is sid (`8:7.1.2.15+dfsg1-1`), which is ImageMagick 7.x
+
+This is a classic scanner false positive caused by package-name matching without validating code-path presence. The FTXT image format is entirely absent from the ImageMagick 6.9.x branch, so the exploit condition cannot be reached.
+
+**Conclusion:** Debian Bookworm ImageMagick 6.9.11.60+dfsg is **not affected** by CVE-2026-25967 (false positive / not applicable to this codebase).
+
+---
+
+## Source Code Verification (CVE-2026-25967)
+
+```bash
+# Verify ftxt source file is absent
+ls src/re-image/imagemagick-6.9.11.60+dfsg/coders/ftxt.c
+# Result: No such file or directory
+
+# Search for any FTXT references in the entire source tree
+grep -ri "ftxt" src/re-image/imagemagick-6.9.11.60+dfsg/
+# Result: No matches (only the patch file itself)
+
+# Verify ReadInt/ReadChar functions do not exist in any coder
+grep -r "ReadInt\|ReadChar" src/re-image/imagemagick-6.9.11.60+dfsg/coders/
+# Result: No matches
+
+# Verify no FTXT registration in build system
+grep -i "ftxt" src/re-image/imagemagick-6.9.11.60+dfsg/configure.ac
+grep -i "ftxt" src/re-image/imagemagick-6.9.11.60+dfsg/coders/Makefile.am
+# Result: No matches in either file
+```
+
+Observed behavior during validation:
+
+- The patch references `coders/ftxt.c` which does not exist in ImageMagick 6.9.11.60
+- Quilt stops with "No file to patch" because the target file is missing
+- No equivalent FTXT symbol (`RegisterFTXTImage`, `ReadFTXTImage`, `ReadInt`, `ReadChar`) is present in any source file
+- The FTXT format is a 7.x-only feature with no 6.x counterpart
+
