+# Why CVE-2026-25794 in ImageMagick 6 (Debian Bookworm) Is a False Positive
+
+## Overview: What Is the UHDR Coder?
+
+CVE-2026-25794 affects the **UHDR (Ultra HDR)** image coder in ImageMagick. The vulnerability is in `WriteUHDRImage` in `coders/uhdr.c`, which uses 32-bit `int` arithmetic to compute the pixel buffer size. UHDR support was added only in **ImageMagick 7**; the ImageMagick 6 codebase never included this coder. Security scanners and the [Debian security tracker](https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2026-25794) may flag the Bookworm package `8:6.9.11.60+dfsg-1.6+deb12u6` as vulnerable because no fixed 6.x version is published—only **sid** has a fixed release (`8:7.1.2.15+dfsg1-1`). This document explains why that package is a **false positive**: the vulnerable code is not present, so the issue is **not exploitable** on Debian Bookworm’s ImageMagick 6.
+
+---
+
+## Why CVE-2026-25794 Is a False Positive for Debian Bookworm
+
+Security scanners (e.g., Trivy, Grype) and the Debian security tracker may flag **CVE-2026-25794** for ImageMagick 6.9.11.60 on Bookworm, but:
+
+- The vulnerability lives in **`coders/uhdr.c`**, which exists only in the **ImageMagick 7** tree.
+- Debian’s Bookworm source for `imagemagick` **does not ship `uhdr.c`**—the [coders directory](https://sources.debian.org/src/imagemagick/8:6.9.11.60+dfsg-1.6+deb12u6/coders/) for `8:6.9.11.60+dfsg-1.6+deb12u6` has no UHDR coder.
+- Without `WriteUHDRImage`, there is **no code path** that performs the flawed size calculation or the out-of-bounds write.
+- Tracker status is “vulnerable” for policy (no fixed 6.x release); **actual exploitability** is **none** for this package.
+
+---
+
+# CVE Breakdown
+
+---
+
+## CVE-2026-25794 – Heap Buffer Overflow in `WriteUHDRImage` (ImageMagick 7 Only)
+
+- **Component:** ImageMagick (`coders/uhdr.c` — **ImageMagick 7 only**)
+- **Issue:** `WriteUHDRImage` uses `int` arithmetic to compute the pixel buffer size. When image dimensions are large, the multiplication overflows 32-bit `int`, causing an undersized heap allocation followed by an out-of-bounds write.
+- **Impact:** Heap buffer overflow → may cause:
+  - Process crash during UHDR image write
+  - Heap corruption
+  - Potential attacker-controlled out-of-bounds heap write
+- **Root Cause:** Integer overflow in buffer size calculation in `coders/uhdr.c`
+- **Upstream Status:** ✅ **Fixed** in ImageMagick **7.1.2-15**  
+  → [GitHub Advisory GHSA-vhqj-f5cj-9x8h](https://github.com/ImageMagick/ImageMagick/security/advisories/GHSA-vhqj-f5cj-9x8h)  
+  → [NVD CVE-2026-25794](https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2026-25794)
+
+---
+
+## Package Status (Debian)
+
+| Debian Release | ImageMagick Version                    | Tracker Status | Actually Exploitable? |
+|----------------|----------------------------------------|----------------|------------------------|
+| Bullseye       | 8:6.9.11.60+dfsg-1.3+deb11u9           | Vulnerable     | ❌ No (no `uhdr.c`)    |
+| Bookworm       | 8:6.9.11.60+dfsg-1.6+deb12u6           | Vulnerable     | ❌ No (no `uhdr.c`)    |
+| Trixie         | 8:7.1.1.43+dfsg1-1+deb13u5             | Vulnerable     | ✅ Yes (has UHDR)      |
+| Sid (unstable) | 8:7.1.2.15+dfsg1-1                     | Fixed          | ✅ Patched             |
+
+---
+
+## Why No Fix Is Required for ImageMagick 6 on Bookworm
+
+- The **vulnerable code** (`coders/uhdr.c` / `WriteUHDRImage`) is **not present** in the ImageMagick 6 source shipped by Debian for Bookworm.
+- Patching or upgrading ImageMagick 6 on Bookworm **does not change** exploitability for this CVE—there is no vulnerable code to fix.
+- Remediation is only relevant for **ImageMagick 7** builds that include the UHDR coder (e.g., Trixie, or custom builds with `--with-uhdr`).
+
+---
+
+### Recommended Fix Strategy
+
+| Environment                      | Fix Strategy |
+|---------------------------------|--------------|
+| Debian Bookworm (ImageMagick 6) | **No action required** — false positive; vulnerable code not present. Use this document for audit justification if needed. |
+| Debian Trixie / Sid (ImageMagick 7) | Upgrade to `8:7.1.2.15+dfsg1-1` or later (sid has the fix). |
+| Custom ImageMagick 7 with UHDR | Upgrade to 7.1.2-15 or later, or backport the [upstream fix](https://github.com/ImageMagick/ImageMagick/commit/ffe589df5ff8ce1433daa4ccb0d2a9fadfbe30ed). |
+
+---
+
+## Summary
+
+- CVE-2026-25794 affects **ImageMagick 7** only (UHDR coder in `coders/uhdr.c`).
+- **Debian Bookworm** ImageMagick 6 (`8:6.9.11.60+dfsg-1.6+deb12u6`) does **not** ship the UHDR coder → **false positive** for exploitability.
+- Tracker may show “vulnerable” for policy; **no patch or workaround** is required for this package.
+- Treat scanner alerts for this CVE on Bookworm’s ImageMagick 6 as **valid in the tracker but not exploitable**—document as false positive where required.
