Description: CVE-2026-30937 - Fix CARD32 arithmetic overflow in WriteXWDImage
 ImageMagick prior to 6.9.13-41 has a 32-bit unsigned integer overflow in
 the XWD encoder. The bytes_per_line calculation uses CARD32 (unsigned 32-bit)
 arithmetic, and the previous truncation check (comparing a value to its own
 CARD32 cast) was unreliable for detecting overflow. An attacker could trigger
 an undersized heap buffer allocation leading to an out-of-bounds heap write
 when writing an extremely large image in XWD format. This patch replaces the
 unreliable truncation check with an explicit 65535 upper bound on image
 dimensions.
Origin: upstream, https://github.com/ImageMagick/ImageMagick6/commit/42e5a37eeb60ca4fdede5060c0aa60802c2dc701
Author: Cristy <urban-warrior@imagemagick.org>
